Class Literal

java.lang.Object

      org.epochx.epox.Literal
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
Direct Known Subclasses:
BooleanERC, DoubleERC, IntegerERC
public class Literal
extends Node

Literal values are nodes with a specific value. Generally, the value of a literal should not change. The difference between a Literal node and a Variable node is subtle. Variable instances cannot be copied, instead, all references to the same variable should refer to the same Variable instance. In contrast, Literal instances may be cloned and behave like most other node types.

See Also:
Variable

clone

public Literal clone()
Creates a new Literal instance which is a copy of this instance. The clone will contain a value which is a reference to the same object as this literal's value. For mutable object values, users should consider extending this class to provide a clone method which can provide an appropriate deep clone.
